Sentencas: A new semi-empirical model is formulated to calculate the potential differences at the cathode/electrolyte and electrolyte/anode interfaces separately for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Theoretical calculation of the electrical potential at the electrode/electrolyte interfaces of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The new model is based on a reduced reaction mechanism, and it accounts for the oxygen ion concentration at these interfaces.
Titulo: Theoretical calculation of the electrical potential at the electrode/electrolyte interfaces of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The model also considers the Gibbs free energy for the two electrode interfaces seperately.
Titulo: Theoretical calculation of the electrical potential at the electrode/electrolyte interfaces of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results from case studies demonstrate the great potential of the proposed model.
Titulo: Theoretical calculation of the electrical potential at the electrode/electrolyte interfaces of solid oxide fuel cells
